I applied to three colleges, all of which would have been acceptable, but I knew my favorite. Of course, even back in 1979 those applications came with a stiff fee, and although it would have been fun to apply to Harvard or Yale, just as a lark and to see if you'd be accepted, was it really worth the price tag?

